Disadvantages -

1) training multiple models.

Advantages -

1) Improvement in performance.
2) Bias and Variance.
3) Low bias + Low variance.

Bias - caused by over-simplifying the Model -

1) It happens when model makes the strong assumptions about the data.
2) high bias - model is too simple - underfitting.
3) cannot capture underlying pattern.


Variance - too much sensitivity to training data.

1) High variance → model is too complex → overfitting.
2) The model learns noise along with the pattern.
3) Works very well on training data but poorly on new data.

